## Requirement Specification: Residential Cooperative Housing Society Finance

### 1. Purpose
Support tracking and management of:
- recurring maintenance income from residents
- all society expenses
- payment status, balances, and financial reports

---

## 2. Actors
- `Admin` / `Society Secretary`
- `Treasurer` / `Accountant`
- `Resident` / `Member`
- `Board Member`
- `Auditor`

---

## 3. Core Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Unit / Member Management
- Maintain a register of flats/units with:
  - unit number
  - owner name
  - occupant type (owner/tenant)
  - membership status
- Track member contact details and bank/payment preferences
- Manage multiple occupants or joint owners

### 3.2 Maintenance Income Management
- Define maintenance charges:
  - monthly/quarterly/annual frequency
  - amount per unit or calculated by area/flat type
  - additional levies (sinking fund, repair fund, water, electricity)
- Generate maintenance invoices automatically
- Apply late fees / interest for overdue payments
- Record payments:
  - mode: cash, cheque, online transfer, UPI, bank deposit
  - date, amount, reference number
- Auto-allocate payments to:
  - current maintenance
  - arrears
  - penalty
  - special fund
- Show member ledger with:
  - total due
  - amount paid
  - balance
  - historical payments

### 3.3 Expense Tracking
- Create expense categories:
  - repairs/maintenance
  - salaries
  - utilities
  - property tax
  - insurance
  - administrative
- Record expense entries with:
  - date, amount, vendor/supplier
  - expense category
  - payment status (paid/unpaid)
  - approval status
  - supporting documents
- Support recurring expenses and approvals
- Maintain vendor/supplier master data

### 3.4 Budgeting and Forecasting
- Define annual budgets by category
- Compare actual expenses vs budget
- Forecast cash flow for upcoming periods
- Track reserve/sinking fund balances

### 3.5 Receivables and Payables
- Maintain incoming maintenance receivables
- Track outstanding dues by member/unit
- Generate collection status reports
- Track payable expenses and vendor due dates

### 3.6 Reporting and Dashboards
- Dashboard with:
  - total maintenance collected
  - current arrears
  - upcoming due invoices
  - recent expenses
  - fund balances
- Standard reports:
  - monthly maintenance collection
  - expenses by category
  - profit & loss / cash flow
  - arrears statement
  - unit-wise outstanding
  - bank reconciliation
- Export reports to PDF / Excel

### 3.7 Notifications and Communication
- Send reminders for due/overdue maintenance
- Issue payment receipts
- Notify residents of new charges or society notices

### 3.8 Audit and History
- Keep audit trail of:
  - transaction creation
  - edits
  - approvals
  - payments
- Record user ID, timestamp, action details

---

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Accuracy
- Ensure financial calculations are precise
- Validate payment amounts and dates

### 4.2 Security
- Role-based access control
- Secure login and password management
- Data confidentiality for member financial records

### 4.3 Reliability
- Data backup and restore
- Transaction safety and consistency

### 4.4 Usability
- Simple entry forms for expenses and payments
- Clear status indicators for dues and arrears
- Easy search/filter for units, invoices, expenses

### 4.5 Compliance
- Support statutory requirements for cooperative societies
- Maintain records suitable for audit

---

## 5. Optional Enhancements
- Mobile app / responsive web portal for residents
- Online payment integration
- SMS / email payment reminders
- Multi-society support in one system
- Multi-currency support if needed

---

## 6. Minimum Data Elements
- Member: name, flat, contact, membership number
- Invoice: period, amount, due date, status
- Payment: date, amount, mode, reference
- Expense: category, vendor, amount, date, approval
- Fund: maintenance, reserve, sinking, contingency

